});

 A pseudo-class in CSS is used to define a special state of an element. For example.. it can style an element when the user interacts with it or when it meets certain conditions (like being the first child of its parent).
Examples:
:hover: Applies styles when an element is hovered over by the user.
:nth-child(): Selects elements based on their position in a parent element.
:focus: Applies styles when an element is focused.. such as an input field.
css
Copy code
